						               													<description>Object of the game is to be the first to get rid of your cards by dressing Cleon, the chameleon&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists 48 cards which can be either a head or body, or tail for 16 different chameleons. Each creature will be 2 colors (unique combination), but each of these colors will be found on other chameleons, in different combinations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Early in the game, the dealer prepares a single chameleon, with elements of the same color, it raises the center of the table. The cards are then shuffled and the dealer deals eight cards to each participant.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, the active player will try play one of his cards to replace a body part of the chameleon in the middle of the table. &amp;#10;- this card must be the same body part as the removed card. &amp;#10;- this card must have a color in common with one of the neighboring cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the active player can't play, he draws one card and passes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player who gets rid of his cards first is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
